# The vendored frontend-design bundle needs LF pinned so the working copy
# stays byte-identical to its upstream source regardless of core.autocrlf
# (`true` on Windows checkouts) — TEMPLATE-CHANGELOG v2.4.8. It no longer
# needs a rule of its OWN: the bundle left the TS/Next profile for base/ in
# v2.7.6 and moved on to base/.agents/skills/frontend-design/ in v2.8.0, and
# both the base/.gitattributes `* text=auto eol=lf` pin (v2.6.0) and the
# harness-kit/** pin below already cover every copy of it. The rule that used
# to sit here named profiles/typescript-next/skills/frontend-design/**, a path
# that stopped existing in v2.7.6 — it protected nothing for two rounds.
# Verify a move with: git check-attr text eol -- <the vendored file>.

# Parity-tested mirror pairs must materialize IDENTICALLY on every
# platform: base/.gitattributes (v2.6.0) pins base/** to LF, so its
# byte-for-byte twins — harness-kit/ and the root-homed SETUP.md — need
# the same pin, or a fresh Windows checkout (autocrlf=true) writes CRLF
# on one side only and test_kit_parity reads phantom drift. Still scoped:
# the repo-wide line-ending call remains unmade.
harness-kit/** text=auto eol=lf
/SETUP.md text eol=lf

# The pre-push guard shim is a sh script git executes directly: a CRLF
# checkout breaks it (sh chokes on \r, shebang included), so the guard
# pair stays LF everywhere. Still scoped: the repo-wide line-ending
# call remains unmade.
.githooks/** text eol=lf
